"{\"uid\": \"wbay.com-2024-07-26-hshs-st-vincent-dresses-up-nicu-babies-spirit-olympics\", \"text\": \"GREEN BAY, Wis. (WBAY) - Babies in the newborn intensive care unit (NICU) at HSHS St. Vincent Children's Hospital in Green Bay are showing their Olympic spirit!  NICU babies were dressed up in red, white, and blue gear, sweatbands, medals and even training shoes to get into the spirit of the international games.  \\\"Every day, our NICU babies at HSHS St. Vincent Children's Hospital inspire us with their strength and resilience,\\\" said James Burke, Manager, of HSHS St. Vincent Children's Hospital NICU. \\\"Every milestone they achieve is a victory worth celebrating!\\\"  HSHS St. Vincent Children's Hospital also cheers on its team of NICU professionals who help get every baby off to the best possible start in life. Neonatologists, neonatal nurse practitioners, registered nurses, developmental therapists, lactation consultants, respiratory therapists, and social workers, provide 24/7 care for infants born prematurely, with low birth weights, congenital birth defects, and unanticipated complications during delivery.  HSHS St. Vincent Children's Hospital's NICU is labeled as the first, largest, and longest-serving NICU in the Green Bay region.  Copyright 2024 WBAY. All rights reserved.\"}"